			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Polyvinylpyrrolidone (PVP), also commonly called polyvidone or povidone, is a water-soluble polymer compound made from the monomer N-vinylpyrrolidone. It is available in a range of molecular weights and related viscosities. It is a chemically inert solid polymer used chiefly in medicine as a vehicle for drugs. It is used in the pharmaceutical industry as a synthetic polymer vehicle for dispersing and suspending drugs.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">聚乙烯吡咯烷酮（PVP）通常也称为聚维酮或聚维酮，是一种水溶性高分子化合物，由单体 N-乙烯基吡咯烷酮制成。它具有不同的分子量和相关粘度。它是一种化学惰性固体聚合物，主要用于医药领域，是药物的载体。它在制药业中用作分散和悬浮药物的合成聚合物载体。</common:generalComment>
